{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Gal|6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","chapter":6,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:6:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":6,"verse":1,"text":"Brothers and sisters, if someone is overtaken in any wrongdoing, you who are spiritual, restore such a person with a gentle spirit, watching out for yourselves so that you also won’t be tempted.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:6:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":6,"verse":2,"text":"Carry one another’s burdens; in this way you will fulfill the law of Christ.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:6:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":6,"verse":3,"text":"For if anyone considers himself to be something when he is nothing, he deceives himself.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:6:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":6,"verse":4,"text":"Let each person examine his own work, and then he can take pride in himself alone, and not compare himself with someone else.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:6:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":6,"verse":5,"text":"For each person will have to carry his own load.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:6:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":6,"verse":6,"text":"Let the one who is taught the word share all his good things with the teacher.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:6:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":6,"verse":7,"text":"Don’t be deceived: God is not mocked. For whatever a person sows he will also reap,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:6:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":6,"verse":8,"text":"because the one who sows to his flesh will reap destruction from the flesh, but the one who sows to the Spirit will reap eternal life from the Spirit.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:6:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":6,"verse":9,"text":"Let us not get tired of doing good, for we will reap at the proper time if we don’t give up.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:6:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":6,"verse":10,"text":"Therefore, as we have opportunity, let us work for the good of all, especially for those who belong to the household of faith.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:6:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":6,"verse":11,"text":"Look at what large letters I use as I write to you in my own handwriting.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:6:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":6,"verse":12,"text":"Those who want to make a good impression in the flesh are the ones who would compel you to be circumcised —but only to avoid being persecuted for the cross of Christ.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:6:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":6,"verse":13,"text":"For even the circumcised don’t keep the law themselves, and yet they want you to be circumcised in order to boast about your flesh.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:6:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":6,"verse":14,"text":"But as for me, I will never boast about anything except the cross of our Lord Jesus Christ. The world has been crucified to me through the cross, and I to the world.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:6:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":6,"verse":15,"text":"For both circumcision and uncircumcision mean nothing; what matters instead is a new creation.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:6:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":6,"verse":16,"text":"May peace come to all those who follow this standard, and mercy even to the Israel of God!","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:6:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":6,"verse":17,"text":"From now on, let no one cause me trouble, because I bear on my body the marks of Jesus.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:6:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","bookOrder":47,"chapter":6,"verse":18,"text":"Brothers and sisters, the grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with your spirit. Amen.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Gal","chapter":6,"paragraphStarts":[1,6,11,17],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"Carry One Another’s Burdens"},{"beforeVerse":11,"text":"Concluding Exhortation"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:6:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Brothers and sisters, if someone is overtaken in any wrongdoing, you who are spiritual, restore such a person with a gentle "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jms 3:13","book":"Jas","chapter":3,"verse":13,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" spirit, "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Or with the Spirit of gentleness"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 51:12","book":"Psa","chapter":51,"verse":12,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" watching out for yourselves so that you also won’t be tempted. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jms 1:13","book":"Jas","chapter":1,"verse":13,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jms 3:13","book":"Jas","chapter":3,"verse":13},{"label":"Ps 51:12","book":"Psa","chapter":51,"verse":12},{"label":"Jms 1:13","book":"Jas","chapter":1,"verse":13}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Or with the Spirit of gentleness"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:6:2","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Carry one another’s burdens; in this way you will fulfill the law of Christ. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Co 9:21","book":"1Co","chapter":9,"verse":21,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Co 9:21","book":"1Co","chapter":9,"verse":21}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:6:3","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"For if anyone considers himself to be something when he is nothing, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Co 3:18","book":"1Co","chapter":3,"verse":18,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Co 12:11","book":"2Co","chapter":12,"verse":11,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gl 2:6","book":"Gal","chapter":2,"verse":6,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" he deceives himself. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Co 3:18","book":"1Co","chapter":3,"verse":18},{"label":"2Co 12:11","book":"2Co","chapter":12,"verse":11},{"label":"Gl 2:6","book":"Gal","chapter":2,"verse":6}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Gal:6:4","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Let each person examine his own work, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mk 14:6","book":"Mrk","chapter":14,"verse":6,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gl 3:10","book":"Gal","chapter":3,"verse":10,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jms 2:14","book":"Jas","chapter":2,"verse":14,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" and then he can take pride in himself alone, and not compare himself with someone else. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Mk 14:6